1. Coinbase adds MORPHO and PYTH to the coin listing roadmap;
2. BNB Chain will launch the first round of $4.4 million Meme coin liquidity support plan, which will officially start on February 18;
3. Bitcoin network transaction volume has dropped to a 12-month low, down 55% from the peak;
4. Tether is actively communicating with US lawmakers on the stablecoin regulatory bill, which may be signed into law by Trump in April;
5. Arca, a division of the New York Stock Exchange, has applied to the SEC to "allow Grayscale's Ethereum ETF to be pledged";
6. The US SEC Crypto Working Group requested a 28-day extension to respond to Coinbase's appeal;
7. Andre Cronje: Meme coin participants do not care about DeFi or even blockchain at all, and are not crypto user groups;
8. ai16z released the ElizaOS framework roadmap;
9. swarms: Launchpad Beta version is online, and users can conduct AI Agent Tokenization;
10. In the past 7 days, 3.8 billion USDCs were issued, and the circulation increased by about 300 million;
11. The US Senate accused the founder of Pantera of cashing out more than 1 billion US dollars from immigration and failing to pay taxes normally;
12. Magic Eden: Unclaimed ME tokens have been airdropped to the wallets of pledged users;
13. The Argentine president explained the reason for deleting the tweet: he did not understand the token project and had nothing to do with the LIBRA project;
14. KIP Protocol: LIBRA is a private enterprise project, and Argentine President Mile did not participate in the development;
15. The team behind LIBRA has cashed out 107 million US dollars;
16. LIBRA tokens are only registered on Moonshot instead of platform verification, which is the latest feature of the platform.

Odaily Planet Daily News According to Farside Investors, the US Bitcoin spot ETF had a net inflow of US$70.6 million yesterday, including:
BlackRock IBIT: +US$22.3 million;
Fidelity FBTC: +US$94 million;
Bitwise BITB: +US$8 million;
ARK ARKB: -US$13.2 million;
Grayscale GBTC: -US$47 million;
Grayscale Mini BTC: +US$6.5 million.
